    </div>
</ReuCenter>
<ReuCenter>
    <section id="installation">
        <h3>Installation guide</h3>
        <p>First, make sure you bought <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/developer/nadeo/list/34687/">all 4 TrackMania 2 games</a> and registered them in your ManiaPlanet account. You can buy them from Steam or Ubisoft Store and mix them however you want.</p>
        <p>If <b>Install in ManiaPlanet</b> doesn't do anything, that means the ManiaPlanet protocol isn't working for you. You can activate it by installing the <a href="https://maniaplanet.com/download">standalone ManiaPlanet version</a>.</p>
        <p>In case you don't want to install the title pack this way, below are other options. <b>In case the title pack updates very slowly, use Option 3.</b></p>
        <div class="options">
            <div>
                <h4>Option 1 - Install in title store</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open ManiaPlanet (or any Trackmania 2 game)</li>
                    <li>At the bottom, click on an empty frame with heaven on it (that's called 'station')</li>
                    <li>Click FROM THE STORE</li>
                    <li>You might already see ENVIMIX Turbo there. In case not, click on TRENDING and scroll through different categories and pages.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h4>Option 2 - Install from URL</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open ManiaPlanet (or any Trackmania 2 game)</li>
                    <li>At the bottom, click on an empty frame with heaven on it (that's called 'station')</li>
                    <li>Click FROM URL</li>
                    <li>Enter this text: <code>envimix:turbo</code></li>
                    <li>Click OK</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h4>Option 3 - Install manually</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click <b>Download manually</b> on this page, or just <a href="turbo/download">here</a>.</li>
                    <li>Put the downloaded Pack.Gbx file to the <code>Documents/ManiaPlanet/Packs</code> folder. In case you're updating, close ManiaPlanet first.</li>
                    <li>Open ManiaPlanet (or any Trackmania 2 game)</li>
                    <li>At the bottom, click on an empty frame with heaven on it (that's called 'station')</li>
                    <li>Click FROM DISK</li>
                    <li>Look for the ENVIMIX Turbo package, click on it, and load it</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</ReuCenter>

